parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the vehicle vibrates or kicks back when braking
the brakes fail to respond or are slow to respond
the vehicle takes longer than usual to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially on slippery or uneven road surfaces.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the brakes fail to respond or are slow to respond
the vehicle loses traction or stability
the brakes vibrate or pulse when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes fail to respond or are slow to respond
the vehicle takes longer than usual to stop
the brake fluid level is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brakes to be difficult to apply, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the brakes require excessive force to apply
the vehicle takes longer than usual to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
despite the driver's attempts to slow down
and may only respond to the application of the parking brake or shutting off the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty speed sensor can cause the vehicle's speed control system to malfunction, leading to unintended acceleration or other safety issues.
symptoms: The vehicle's speedometer may not function correctly
or the vehicle may experience sudden and unexplained changes in speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noisy seat belt buckles can be distracting and annoying, potentially causing driver distraction, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The seat belt buckles make noise
clicking or rattling sounds when in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to adjust the middle right bench seat lap belt can compromise the safety of the occupant, increasing the risk of injury in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The middle right bench seat lap belt is impossible to adjust due to its design
making it difficult or impossible to secure the occupant properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden separation of the roof rack from the vehicle can cause loose items to fall onto the road, creating a hazard for other drivers and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The roof rack becomes detached from the vehicle while driving
items on the roof rack fall onto the road
loud noise or rattling sound from the roof rack area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor performance of the air conditioner compressor can lead to reduced cooling capacity, increased noise, and potentially cause the compressor to fail, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: The air conditioner blows warm air
the air conditioner is noisy
the compressor is making a loud or unusual sound
the air conditioner is not cooling the vehicle effectively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the slide/side door window can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and reduced visibility, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The slide/side door window does not open or close properly
the window is stuck in an open or closed position
the window makes unusual noises or vibrations
the window has excessive wind noise or leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can reduce visibility during rain, snow, or other inclement weather conditions, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The windshield wipers do not turn on
the wipers move slowly or erratically
the wipers leave streaks or residue on the windshield
the wipers make unusual noises or vibrations.
